DIGEST
SB 346 Engrossed 2026 Regular Session Barrow
Proposed law prohibits a student, faculty member, member of the administrative staff, or
other employee at an elementary or secondary school from using deepfake material against
a student enrolled in K-12, with the intent to coerce, harass, intimidate, or maliciously
disseminate or sell the material.
Proposed law provides for the definition of "deepfake".
Proposed law authorizes BESE, in collaboration with the Dept. of Education, to develop and
adopt rules and regulations to implement the provisions of proposed law.
Effective on August 1, 2026.
(Adds R.S. 17:416.14.1)
